CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1780143067
OL,3,CMan and woman deny murder of 'giggly
OL,4,Cand happy' toddler
OL,6,FThe pair appeared at Leicester Crown
OL,7,FCourt on Friday, 29 May where they
OL,8,Fdenied all the charges.
OL,10,FIn a tribute, Tobias' father Simon
OL,11,FDoyle said his son put a smile on
OL,12,Feveryone's face.
OL,14,FHe said: "Tobias was my best friend.
OL,15,FHe was a giggly, happy little boy who
OL,16,Fput a smile on everyone's face.
OL,18,F"He had the most beautiful chubby
OL,19,Fcheeks and curly hair and he
OL,20,Fabsolutely loved dinosaurs.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/4
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,379,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F378A1780143067
OL,3,CMan and woman deny murder of 'giggly
OL,4,Cand happy' toddler
OL,6,F"We love him and miss him so much."
OL,8,FGordon, of Butterwick Drive, and
OL,9,FMorgan, of Morledge Street, are
OL,10,Fexpected to face a trial, lasting
OL,11,Feight weeks, in front of a High Court
OL,12,Fjudge on 25 January next year.
OL,14,FJudge Timothy Spencer KC told Gordon
OL,15,Fand Morgan they would next have to
OL,16,Fappear in court in October.
OL,18,FHe said: "You are both in a very
OL,19,Fserious position, I think you both
OL,20,Fknow that.
